RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 18500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Consid ered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DO YA WANNA DANCE was reserved along the rail in the early furlongs, then urged at a steady beat throughout the turn before meeting contenders in the early stretch to tango in the final stage, kicked cleared and was up at the wire to prove the grooviest of them all. BRENTSPENCE settled behind the field down the backstretch and into the top of the turn, began to gain ground gamely heading into the early stretch, shifted to the three path then closed willingly and was up for second. OVERTHETOPJUSTICE was well rated while two wide down the backstretch, then moved along the inside to on the turn, rallied in the early stretch to battle with rivals on the outside down the lane and closed well just missing the place prize. LEO'S ROAR vied with outer rivals from the inside, then inched away to take command heading into the turn, then vied between two rivals in the stretch before giving way grudgingly in the end. SMILE LIKE KYLE battled between rivals while two wide in the early furlongs, continued to menace throughout the turn and into the stretch then gave way in the end. FOR MAMA vied while four wide and between rivals, then made a mild bid on the turn and flattened out in the end. STICKER vied in the three path, bid gamely on the turn between rivals before weakening in the stretch. ELUSIVE WARRIOR vied while five wide down the backstretch and into the turn then flattened out in the stretch.
